postings.body:
Recently signed a 1 year lease in May in a beautiful 3 story condo that is located in a residential neighborhood that is walking distance to parks, runyon canyon, restaurants, shops etc. We are 2 gay guys looking for someone to take over our friends spot that recently accepted a job opportunity over in London and will be moving out the beginning of September. You will be required to take over the remainder of the lease (ends May 2015) as well as provide a refundable $1100 security deposit at move in. Move in date is Sep 7th (might be flexible) and rent is $1100 a month for the master bedroom with its own bathroom (both will be completely empty for your belongings), parking spot, and utilities typically run around $30 for direct tv, cable internet, and your basic water/trash etc.
Condo description:
-3 story condo with side by side parking and a private entrance into the apartment.
-Newer set of washer/dryer in unit
-Private Rooftop
-1st floor (1/2 bath, kitchen, dining room, living room, wet bar)
-2nd floor (master bed/bath + 2 more bedrooms with shared bath)
-3rd floor (Private rooftop with lots of potential that is currently empty)
-Hardwood floor throughout.
-Storage in garage as well as lots of storage throughout the condo.
Description of what we are looking for:
-Female in her mid/late 20s
-Respectful, clean, likes to cook, considerate, gay friendly.
-Young professional that works a day job and respects the same.
-Ideally is looking for something more than just a roommate situation.
-Loves to have laid back movie/tv nights but also doesn`t mind occasionally going out or having friends over.
Little bit about ourselves:
We are both fun loving, positive guys that work during the day and spend a good amount of our nights watching movies and tv, but like to drink/go out on occasion, but are always respectful and considerate of the other persons work schedule. We are close friends that are hoping to get along well with our new roommate and hopefully establish some sort of a friendship with them. Although we are both gay, we are not your typical gay guy that has a revolving door of men coming through and we hope for the same. One of us is 27, currently in the process of lining up a new job as well as starting school at Vidal Sassoon in the fall to pursue being a hair stylist. Loves to workout and tries to live a healthy lifestyle. The other works Mon-Fri 9 to 6 at an advertising agency, plays dodgeball during the week and likes to go out on the weekends.
If you feel like you would be a good fit please feel free to email a brief bio of yourself, what you do for work, what your day to day lifestyle typically looks like, interests/hobbies, and any links to social media that you use.
Due to lots of inquiries we will not be responding to people that do not meet these criteria`s that we are looking for, as well as, that does not provides us with the information that we are asking for.
